BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:5-Eyrki8uefqLLHo3ysNB
SUMMARY:Bosanko Public Lecture on Sustainability and Growth in Developing E
	conomies
DTSTAMP:20260407T043751Z
DTSTART:20260420T230000Z
DESCRIPTION:Seattle University’s Albers School of Business and Economics in
	vites the public to a Bosanko Lecture featuring Aparna Sawhney\, Professor
	 at the Centre for the Study of the World Economy in the School of Interna
	tional Studies at Jawaharlal Nehru University \\(India\\).\n\nIn this acad
	emic public lecture\, Professor Sawhney will examine India’s clean energy 
	transition through the lens of sustainability\, economic growth\, and ener
	gy security in a developing-economy context. As one of the world’s fastest
	-growing economies and home to nearly 1.5 billion people\, India faces the
	 complex challenge of expanding energy access while reducing carbon emissi
	ons and promoting sustainable development.\n\nThe lecture will explore Ind
	ia’s renewable energy policies\, its experience with tradeable clean energ
	y credits\, and emerging approaches to carbon pricing within its broader d
	evelopment strategy. Attendees will gain insight into how policy design\, 
	market mechanisms\, and international trade intersect with climate goals i
	n developing countries.\n\nThe lecture will be followed by a moderated Q&A
	 session. This event is open to students\, faculty\, researchers\, policy 
	professionals\, and members of the public interested in climate policy\, s
	ustainable development\, and global energy transitions.\n\nhttps://seatoda
	y.6amcity.com/events/#/details/bosanko-public-lecture-on-sustainability-an
	d-growth-in-developing-economies/18260268/2026-04-20T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday -
	 All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/bosanko-public-lecture-on
	-sustainability-and-growth-in-developing-economies/18260268/2026-04-20T00
LOCATION:Northwest Worklofts (Commons)\, 107 West Denny Way\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
